Key Match Events: Devin Booker scored 18 points on 6-for-16 shooting, with five assists, three rebounds, and two steals.
The Kings shot 64% from the field and 53% from three, their best shooting performance of the season.
The transition game by the Kings killed any chances of a Suns comeback, especially in the fourth quarter.
Post-Match Reflections: Devin Booker reflected on his performance, stating he could have done a better job of not forcing plays and trusting his teammates more.
The Suns were affected by a depleted roster and playing on a back-to-back, with key players like Bradley Beal and Kevin Durant injured, and Jusuf Nurkic playing hurt.
The Suns' late-night travel from Utah to Sacramento contributed to their tired performance.
